Content:: Arnaldo Pambianco (16 August 1935 – 6 July 2022)[1] was an Italian professional road racing cyclist who was active between 1956 and 1966. The highlight of his career was his overall win in the 1961 Giro d'Italia.[2] He competed at the 1956 Summer Olympics in the road race and finished in seventh individually and fourth with the Italian team.[3]  This biographical article related to an Italian cycling person born in the 1930s is a stub.
